It is an absolutely gorgeous day. The
sun is shining, the water is blue. I'm
about to jump on this boat and go on a
tour of Sunmoon
Lake. I'm out here on the lake now and
it's incredible. The water I feel like
I'm in the Caribbean. It's turquoise.
The entire lake is ringed by these giant
emerald mountains. I can see pagotas off
in the distance. The Wenw Temple. This
place is definitely
magical. Experiencing the lake on the
boat was fantastic. But now I'm going to
go up high in a gondola and get a bird's
eye
view. You can see different villages and
all the different pockets of the lake.
You can really get a sense for how
turquoise the water is. And just
cruising above here, it just
beautiful. I'm looking at a big set of
stairs here. I got to climb to the top,
but I hear it's going to be worth it
because the view from up there is really
nice. Check it out. Totally worth the
hike to the top. And this pigota was
actually built by Changhai Sheek. And he
built it in honor of his mama. So, he's
a big mama's boy. And he made it so that
every time he looked at this, he'd be
reminded of his special mother. Pretty
cool
[Music]
guy. It's been a beautiful day here on
Sunmoon Lake. Got to experience it from
a boat, from high above in a gondola.
And now, beautiful sunset.
